    notes:
      "## Clinical Context — The Mediterranean Diet Anchor\n\nOmega-9 (oleic acid) is the **most abundant fatty acid in human cell membranes globally** and the principal monounsaturated fatty acid in the Mediterranean dietary pattern that has the strongest large-RCT cardiovascular evidence base of any dietary intervention (PREDIMED trial). Despite not being technically essential (humans synthesize oleic acid endogenously), dietary oleic acid combined with EVOO polyphenols provides foundational cardiovascular and metabolic benefit.\n\nThe practical use case spans:\n\n**Mediterranean dietary pattern adherence** — 2-4 tablespoons EVOO daily as part of broader pattern (vegetables, fish, nuts, moderate wine, limited red meat); cardiovascular benefit evidence base is strongest for this pattern\n\n**Saturated fat displacement** — substituting EVOO/avocado oil for refined seed oils OR for excess saturated fat produces modest cardiovascular marker improvement\n\n**Whole-food fat composition** — avocados, macadamia nuts, almonds provide oleic acid alongside other beneficial nutrients\n\n## The EVOO Quality Reality\n\nThe cardiovascular benefit of olive oil is driven substantially by **polyphenols** (oleocanthal, oleuropein, hydroxytyrosol) — not pure oleic acid alone. Quality matters:\n- **Extra virgin olive oil (EVOO)** — cold-pressed, polyphenol-rich, robust flavor, peppery finish (oleocanthal signature), recent harvest date\n- **Refined olive oil / 'pure olive oil' / 'light olive oil' / olive oil blends** — heat-processed, polyphenols stripped or substantially reduced; provides oleic acid without the polyphenol cardiovascular benefit\n- **Olive oil fraud** — substantial issue; many 'extra virgin' labeled products fail independent testing; choose certified brands with documented testing protocols\n\n## The Whole-Food Approach\n\nOmega-9 supplementation is essentially never indicated as capsule — food-source consumption is the principal pattern:\n- **EVOO** — Mediterranean staple; 2-4 tablespoons daily as part of broader pattern\n- **Avocado** — 1/2 to 1 daily; provides oleic acid plus broader nutrition\n- **Macadamia nuts** — 1-2 ounces daily; provides oleic acid plus omega-7 palmitoleic acid plus magnesium\n- **Almonds** — 1-2 ounces daily; oleic acid plus vitamin E\n- **Animal fats from quality sources** — tallow, lard from grass-fed animals; provides oleic acid alongside saturated fats and broader fat-soluble nutrients\n\n## Synergies\n**Omega-3** — paired fatty acid pillar; Mediterranean diet combines both. **Vitamin E** — fat-soluble antioxidant; naturally present in olive oil and nuts. **Mediterranean dietary pattern broadly** — vegetables, fish, nuts, moderate wine, limited red meat. **Low-glycemic carbohydrate intake** — complementary metabolic pattern.\n\n## Evidence Quality\nMechanism characterized; PREDIMED RCT pedigree substantial for Mediterranean diet with EVOO; polyphenol contribution to cardiovascular benefit recognized; food-source approach broadly accessible. Endogenous synthesis means dietary requirement is technical not absolute.\n\n## Research vs Anecdote\nResearch: PREDIMED RCT substantial evidence for Mediterranean diet + EVOO cardiovascular benefit; polyphenol mechanism characterized; foundational fatty acid biochemistry well-established. Anecdote: substantial Mediterranean diet community use base; community recognition of EVOO quality importance; whole-food approach increasingly mainstream. Decision frame: foundational monounsaturated fatty acid; not technically essential but Mediterranean dietary pattern adherence has substantial cardiovascular outcome evidence; EVOO quality matters substantially for polyphenol content; food-source approach (EVOO + avocado + macadamia + almonds) is the principal pattern; capsule supplementation rarely indicated; the catalog does not provide specific protocol guidance per locked HRT/protocol rule.",
